ror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Lexington was born in 1130, in Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert Lexington. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Robert Lexington. He died in 1165, in Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1130–1165":"1130–1165","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1165–1250":"1165–1250","1075–Male":"1075–Surnud","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1075":"1075","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1130–1165":"1130–1165","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1165–1250":"1165–1250","1075–Male":"1075–Kuollut","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1075":"1075","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1130–1165":"1130–1165","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","1165–1250":"1165–1250","1075–Male":"1075–Décédé","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1075":"1075","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Lexington est né en 1130, à Tuxford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Robert Lexington. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. Robert Lexington. Il est décédé en 1165, à Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 35 ans."},"de":{"1130–1165":"1130–1165","1150–Female":"1150–Verstorben","1165–125